comments.body:
Thank you for reaching out.

Note that it is concerning if the digests don't match (i.e., the error looks serious to me).  I think we could add a flag (e.g., `--continue-on-error`) that would allow for continuing the operation and turns errors non-fatal.  But we need to continue the current behavior to remain backwards compatible.

@lsm5 @rhatdan WDYT?
